post_text: Morton ISD has purchased several disinfecting foggers to add an additional measure in our facility cleaning process. Disinfectant fogging involves saturating an entire room with a microbial substance that can purify and remove pathogens from the air, as well as from surfaces within the room. Disinfectant fogging is highly effective at combating pathogens, particularly those that are airborne or carried in respiratory droplets, such as the flu virus or COVID-19. This is an additional protection in above our professional GermBlast applications.

Pandemic Electronic Benefit Transfer (P-EBT) is a one-time food benefit for families who lost access to free or reduced-price meals due to school closures. Eligible P-EBT families will receive application instructions from schools in late May. The P-EBT application will open the first week of June.

P-EBT food benefits are for children who received SNAP food benefits for March 2020 and children who are certified for free or reduced-price school meals during the 2019-20 Texas school year. For more information, visit: hhs.texas.gov/PEBT

Tribe,
A student at the elementary school has been diagnosed with Shigellosis. It is not a fatal bacterial infection, but it is contagious and causes some uncomfortable symptoms. Please see the tips below and contact Nurse Stacy or your trusted physician with any concerns. A letter with more information will be sent home today.

*If symptoms persist, your child must be free of diarrhea and fever WITHOUT medications for the past 24 hours.

post_text: Greetings Morton Junior High Parents, The Junior High will have an awards assembly tomorrow, February 21st at 9:40 am in the Gym. The assembly will be for AB honor roll and perfect attendance. Parents are welcome to attend.

post_text: This is a big weekend for MHS. Several FCCLA members will compete at the regional conference. Elena Alvarado is also running for office. FFA members are on the road to San Antonio with their ag mech projects. The Maidens continue chasing gold balls against Sands tomorrow night.
